{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642754"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:43:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:43:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17963"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17963","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17963"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.26,0.09,0.52,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10677"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79211"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10677"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17963"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64563"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7197"},{"type":"tags","id":"7272"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24868"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24872"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79211"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is primarily responsible for raising the eyebrows and wrinkling the forehead?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Procerus","Levator labii superioris","Orbicularis oculi (orbital and palpebral)","Occipitofrontalis","Corrugator supercilli"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccipitofrontalis\u003C/strong\u003E muscle\u0027s function is to raise the eyebrows and wrinkle the forehead. It consists of two parts: the occipital belly, located at the back of the head, and the frontal belly, which is located at the forehead. The frontal belly is primarily involved in the movement described in the stem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eprocerus\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is involved in frowning and pulling the skin between the eyebrows downward, contributing to the formation of horizontal lines over the bridge of the nose.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elevator labii superioris\u003C/strong\u003E elevates the upper lip, not the eyebrows or forehead.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eorbicularis oculi\u003C/strong\u003E muscle closes the eyelids and is not involved in raising the eyebrows or wrinkling the forehead.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecorrugator supercilli\u003C/strong\u003E muscle draws the eyebrows downward and medially, creating vertical wrinkles above the nose, which is associated with frowning.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The occipitofrontalis\u0027 action is to raise the eyebrows and wrinkle the forehead.","The occipitofrontalis muscle consists of two parts: the occipital belly and the frontal belly.","The facial nerve innervates occipitofrontalis"],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevis